rComments: He explains all concepts clearly and with many examples, making the course content seem pretty easy. He is always open to answer questions and re-explain things in class. To do well, you need to do practice problems such as previous years' exams.

I don't have anything negative to say about Dr. Karouma, he is a good professor. To succeed in this course go over his lectures, and do as many practice questions as you can(he posts a lot of them) - this ensures you understand the material properly! I don't think I'm great at math and doing this has helped tremendously! P. S MASTER REF AND RREF

Watch all of the lectures and review old midterms and you should do fine. (Learn REF and RREF before the start of the course, it will help you a lot). Homework isnt mandatory and not really necessary unless you are really struggling with the content. If you are looking for a good teacher, pick this prof

I had this professor's math class online in fall 2021. He is a good professor in my opinion, but his exams were all multiple choice and there were 10 questions usually so each question was worth a lot of points. It was really hard to get a good grade because of this situation.
Great professor. He is better than most of the maths teachers. Highly recommend.
Great prof! I didn't go to all the classes but he posted all his lectures back on bright space and OneNote was superb. Probably the best calc prof you can get.

Amazing prof, good lectures, and he always posts helpful notes. Fun and entertaining lectures. Pretty easy A if you listen to all the lectures and do Mobius assignment by yourself. Would definitely take one of his classes again

His lectures are so clear that I rarely used the textbook as supplemental readings, but practice as much as you can! Both the old exams and textbook exercises are similar to the test questions. Practice those and you'll be fine (and make use of the Onenote Dropbox!). The only downside is that he often decided to do the lectures asynchronously.

Prof Karouma adapted very well to online learning. His lectures are clear and gives lots of examples during his lectures, which is definitely key for calc. He posts his lecture notes which is helpful. The material on exams is a bit tougher than what is covered in class, but to do well in calc you obviously have to actually practice outside class.
Great lecturer but it's hard to get good grades .
He was great but the questions in the exam are totally different from assignments, and practice questions.

I am not sure about MAT 1341 but for MAT1320 he was great. The only problem was he didn't post sample test for some mid-term tests. But he posted a lot of practice problems and his lectures were easy to understand. You can ask question if u didn't understand the materials during his lectures.

Truly awful. He explained the computations but not the concepts. It was like learning how to screw in a light bulb without knowing what a lightbulb is. Also, he adapted to online teaching horribly and was overall my worst prof in my first term.

I can't speak for in-person classes, but he's an awful online professor. Reads straight from the textbook, doesn't answer questions when asked to provide other examples in class, no office hours. His lectures are supposed to be synchronous and half the time he cancels the day of and posts them at 10pm that night or not until the next day.

He is an excellent lecturer, and his lecture will make you understand Calculus. The only Big Problem was no practice midterm/finals, and so the exams were kind of out in the left field. The grading of the exams was also tough, taking marks off for small mistakes. Overall, a great prof, but get ready to work.

His lectures are very straight forward and understandable. Go to the DGD's they help a lot in your success of the course. He really cares about the students and he tries to help as much as he can. Take this prof if you have the choice !!
Best prof I've ever had. People were complaining that the the second midterm and final were hard but it was pretty easy if you did the homework and attended lectures.

Best professor ever. Seriously, I don't think I could've had a better prof for this class. He is just amazing and shows examples for the entirety of the class to make sure you understand. He is extremely nice and helpful. His second midterm was fairly hard, his final was hard as well. You need to do as many practice problems as possible.

Honestly, probably one of the best profs I had during my first semester of uni, made the transition soooo much easier. I just went to class, followed through the lectures (which are perfect for calc, explains concepts then does a bunch of problems), and did the textbook questions. Not a hard course at all. Amazing prof, wish i had him for calc 2/3.

Really good explainer, takes a looooot of time going over things in detail. I think he's so sweet for taking time out of his day to hold exam review days. First midterm was easy, second midterm and final were hard af... I feel like the final was unnecessarily hard, so you should practice a lot.

Karouma is my best prof this semester for sure! His lessons are clear and concise, and he really knows what he is talking about. He should be a full time prof at UOttawa, it would be great to have him for my other classes in the future.

A great professor that knows what he's doing. Really cares about his students and makes himself available for help all the time. All professors should follow his lead. I hope he teaches for the many years to come.

He set the bar so high I'm not sure another math prof will ever compare. Professor Abdul is such an amazing prof and he truly cares about his students. He gave students multiple chances to redeem themselves and his review sessions helped out a lot. He was always willing to clarify in cases of confusion. I would strongly recommend him.
Amazing professor; he is extremely caring and truly cares about his students. The class is overall easy yet it gives you strong mathematical basis for your future courses

Professor Karouma is hands down one of the most caring professors I have ever come across. He really tries his best to ensure everyone gets a chance to fully understand the course material and even spends his own time outside of office hours to hold review sessions to allow students to ask help for any difficulties they may have. He's amazing.

AN excellent prof who really cares about students, so many times I though i failed his midterms, but ended up with a really high mark. I didn't do to well on the final but still ended with a good grade.

Professor Karouma is an excellent prof! He is super sweet and he is always there for his students. He goes really in depth for his lectures to ensure you get the material, DON'T BE AFRAID TO ASK QUESTIONS, no matter how dumb it is! He won't judge you and he will make sure you get the concept. Wish he could teach all the math classes!
The prof is pretty good. He is fairly flexible with his teaching style as long as you tell him about it. Would recommend!

Prof Karouma is great! During lectures he constantly reminds you of any laws or identities etc which really helps you grasp the material. His midterms are clear and the assignments are well written as well. He's also there for his students and sets up extra classes on the weekends if there is a demand. Definitely recommend taking his course.

New to teaching and I was a bit skeptical at first cause of his accent and lack of experience but he knows what he's doing and doing it quite well and he's always willing to assist anyone when they need it. Would definitely take again.

Even though he seems like he's new to teaching, he's doing a really great job at it. he is VERY clear and goes through everything one step at a time. He even goes out of his way to make extra practice classes before midterms. overall he's a really great prof. Plus he has a great sense of fashion! Hope he gives MAT1332
Posts lecture information online.
He needs a bit more teaching practice, but give him a chance :)
Nice pro
Good prof, explains everything well, good lectures
A little fast for my paste, but a good teacher.
His lectures were clear and concise.

He is the first prof I've had an he has set expectations high. He posts all his lectures online in case you didn't copy something down or you weren't able to make it to class. He noticed that students were struggling so he held extra sessions on the weekend for more review before the midterm. He is very nice too!
Very clear when he speaks. Extra practice session helped. overall good prof
He is very knowledgeable in his lectures . He is confident, and convincing . No doubt, he know  the subject.

He teaches the course really well. He is organized and his step-by-step approach is easy to follow. He gives extra lectures before midterms which shows his dedication to educating his students and making sure they fully understand the content. He has some funny jokes on his assignment too. Great teacher, I hope he stays in uOttawa.

Very enthusiastic about what he does! He's very approachable for any questions. He really wants you to understand the concepts.  He's very organized with his lessons, which makes it easy to understand and keep up in class. This was one class I don't feel like the lessons were being rushed.  He's probably one of the best profs I've had this year
He is very clear and helpful.
This Prof is amazing, he makes sure every one follows up with him and even goes as far as giving up his time to have extra classes. He's great!
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Might seem to drag on at times because he really starts at the VERY basics but it is extremely helpful when you get to the more complicated concepts. Also extremely helpful and really goes all out to help students, even scheduling extra lecture if people still feel like they need help. Definitely TAKE THIS PROF

Really enjoy this Prof. provides lots of example questions for every lecture, is very clear in what content is going to be on the exam and gives a very good exam review. You can really tell he wants to give every student the chance to do well
very kind
He is very helpful and even offered extra help on Friday's and Saturday's! Would recommend this prof! He cares a lot :)
He is amazing!! He makes sure to go through course material thoroughly all the while making sure his students understand what he is teaching as well!!

He is AMAZING!!!!!!!!!!!! Literally, he goes the extra mile just to make sure EVERY student understands even if you didn't cover the previous prerequisite material. He really tries his best!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
He knows how to help without being asked for help
He cares about his students passing the class. Makes an effort to make sure that his students will understand the concepts.
very good
Great professor, really cares about the success of his students. Easy A+ class if you've done grade 12 calculus.

Prof Abdul is great! Very helpful - he takes the time to make sure that everyone understands the coursework. He makes sure that everyone understands the basics really well before going on to harder concepts.
He's always there to help his students, even going out of his way to make more office hour times and extra lectures before midterms. I never really understood math until I had him as a professor
Very young and enthusiastic prof. He really cares  about his students. I liked him
